,Recommended,265610,24510250,"Posted: 24 July, 2016",all,Xana100,"So lemme just get some facts and biases straight.The first game I ever played from Matt was Brawl Royale - a simple flash game that's basically just a reflex game to see how fast you can press a button when prompted. The animation, for me at the time, was pretty dang good and he gained a fan from that moment on. I've played every other game that came out since then, other than the Bullet Heaven ones, and I loved all of them.If you ever get to read this, Matt, I gotta say thanks for entertaining me for all these years. Hopefully, EBF5 will blow EBF4 right out the water.Tl;dr - I'm a fanboy and this review may be a little biased. Also, this is my first ever review.NOW ON TO THE REVIEW!REVIEW:This game was originally a flash game that was (and still is) free to play on sites such as Kongregate and Newgrounds. The only real differences between the free version and the Steam one/Kongregate's premium one are the additional weapons, armors, and badges and Battle Mountain. This is a little underwhelming for something worth $12 dollars, I have to admit.If you've played any traditional JRPG games before, that's pretty much what this game plays like. This may be a turn-off for some, but for fans and newcomers to the genre, I think you'll be in for a treat.The characters are all unique and interesting in their own way - even the NPCs, while not really memorable, have some choice bits of dialogue. As for the dialogue and text in the game, it's very humorous with loads of little nods and jabs to all things video games.The plot is pretty linear, so NG+ is really only for maxing out whatever skill you didn't learn and trying out some new tactics....That's all I can think of at the moment while typing this up so...Overall, 8.5/10 - needs more boobs"
