,Recommended,265610,27070278,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Goldfire64,This is a great soild game. I orignally played this game on Newgrounds and was excited that it was getting a steam release. What makes this game work is that at its core gameplay there is a solid foundation of turn based rpg. This game honeslty feels more solid than some AAA rpgs that come out. The mechanics of elemental strengths and resistances works well. You mix up your skills and equipment to have the correct element to hurt them while trying to have defense that is resitant to the element they are attacking with. On top of the solid gameplay there is the cute aesthetic. This game has a cute charm that makes it very likable. There is also a fair amount of humor that is both it's own jokes as well as references to other video games. The steam version adds in some equipment and an extra mode where you can fight harder versions of the bosses and other enemies. Overall a very fun game.
