,Recommended,265610,17357244,"Posted: 2 August, 2015",all,The Dude,"I love the combat system in this game. It's freeform/organic, has surprising depth and every ability has it's uses. There's a ton of enemy variety on display here and they all have some kind of weakness to exploit. Not all of which are the obvious use fire on ice enemy, etc.. The story doesn't take itself seriously in the slightest. Lots of 4th wall breaking and self referential humor. There's a crap ton of hidden items/loot to collect. And for the most part every single new piece of equipment is unique. With it's own stats, element, procs, counters, etc.. The game is pretty linear with a few optional areas to spice things up. And finally, if you crank the difficulty up the game can get pretty challenging. Especially the boss fights. It's easily the best tradition RPG I've come across on steam. Well worth your time."
