76561198072897164,Recommended,265610,17042717,"Posted: 14 July, 2015",all,Gsg,"Look, if you've seen this game's trailer, and seen anything you liked, or even just had the time to look through the screenshots and said ""Hey, this game looks like it might be good."", please just go and buy this game. If you love Final Fantasy, or Chrono Trigger, or Golden Sun, or really any rpg ever I almost guarentee that there is something here for you. The story, while geared more toward the 12-25 age range, is still an enjoyable, simple story that lays itself out nicely throughout the story. The gameplay flows very well, and it is very easy to notice that there was time put into making the characters and abilities balanced and scale throughout the game. While the game can be very easy when using the corresponding elemental rock,paper,scissors equipment to fight enemies, the battles can still be very long and challenging, making the title of ""Epic Battle"" very evident, especially on epic mode. The art is very well done, and the music fits the game incredibly.It's also important to note that the other three games in the series are FREE online, so if you want a primer to what you will be getting you can go play those aswell, which I would also recommend.All in all, this game, and this series, was a great effort by Matt Rosak and HalcyonicfalconX. Fantastic job, and can't wait for Bullet Heaven 2!"
