76561198108162491,Recommended,265610,16586306,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,forsakenphoenix,"Pros+ Beautiful animations, from battle scenes to idle animations+ Hours of gameplay+ Changing armor/weapons changes the appearance of the character+ Lots of additional gameplay in the post-game+ Not just about turned-based combat; many puzzles to solve and secrets to find throughout the gameCons- The lack of a serious plot line might bother someOverall score: 10/10I can honestly only say good things about this game. If you don't believe me, you can always play the free version on Kongregate to see if you'd like it. Some of you might be wondering, ""Why should I pay for a game I can play for free online?"" Here are my two reasons: First, there is a lot of additional gameplay when you buy the version on Steam. It's the same version as the paid version on Kongregate, but this version comes with Steam Trading Cards, which obviously makes it superior. Second, I've been a longtime fan of the series. (My personal favorite is EBF3.) in some ways, I feel like buying this game was thanks to Kupo for all of the hours of fun I spent in all of his games. But seriously, play this game.If you like turn based RPGs, this game will be perfect for you. The animations are beautiful, and the gameplay draws a lot from the Final Fantasy series. I also love how armor, weapons, and accessories called flairs affect the appearance of characters. It's a personal pet peeve of mine when RPGs have armor, but changing the equipped armor doesn't change what the character is wearing. You can see that a lot of effort went into this game.The game doesn't take itself too seriously, so don't expect to be blown away by the plot. There are some immature jokes as well. Neither of these bothered me, but in fairness to the other games I reviewed, I felt obligated to list a con.Regardless, EBF4 is a wonderful game and you should definitely buy it if you like turn-based RPGs."
