,Recommended,265610,14866674,"Posted: 13 March, 2015",all,β CVn,"Ok, so, once upon a time there was this guy named Matt, and he decided ""I'll make an RPG cause why not.""So then Epic Battle Fantasy was made, and it was cool.A few months later, Matt talked to this girl who went by Phyrnna, and was like ""You wanna help me out with this?"" and she was like ""k""So then EBF 2 was made, and it was great.So the, Matt was on his throne of loot, and he was like ""this isn't working"" and so he gave EBF open world mechanics, side quests, and loads of other♥♥♥♥♥♥And so, EBF 3 was made, and it was AWESOME.2 spinoffs later, Matt decided to then just go ""eh screw it"" and made another, this time with more length, sidequests, enemies, equipment, skills, strategy, and of course, amazing goddamn music.And so EBF 4 was made.And it was concluded that the game was ♥♥♥♥ing amazing.Ok, so, actual review:STORYTIMEThe story isn't much to ride home about, but it's enough to keep the game moving along, so it sorta works. It is still moderately engaging, and doesn't just devolve to ""go here because we aren't gonna say"". At least I can still remember what happened in the game.6/10? 6/10.The GraphicsVery colorful, slightly animu style graphics that are all in all nice to look at. Also, goddamn, some of those abilities are amazing visually (mostly the limit breaks).8/10 m8The GameplayMy first runthrough was on normal mode, cause I'm a ♥♥♥♥♥. But I'm currently trying to get through the game on Hard and later on Epic, so yeah.Basically, this game doesn't fall into the common RPG problem of being able to just spam normal attack to win except on bosses or something, and actually requires a large amount of strategy to get through it. You actually need to be able to adapt to situations, and exploit certain weaknesses to be able to defeat certain enemies (ex. That Goddamn Cosmic Monolith)Exploration is also awarded well in this game too. There are several points in the game where backtracking and exploration can be very useful to you, mostly after you get key items. As well, this game has two optional areas, one small and pretty easy, with the other being basically a super dungeon where the enemies scale to your level and you fight some really powerful bosses. (Again, ♥♥♥♥ cosmic monoliths.)Also, there are a metric ton of deifferent pieces of equipment to customize your character with, allowing you to find a way to fit almost any situation by the time you begin the New Game+ runthroughs.Also, the two NG+ runthroughs cause the enemies to level up with you. That's pretty damn awesome.10/10 Am playing againMusicYou ever heard of Phyrnna? No? well you should listen to her songs. The EBF 4 soundtrack, along with the soundtrakcs for EBF 3 and 2 provide some of the best songs I have heard in a video game ever. Weshdoor Concert? Amazing. Derelict Factory of Twisted Metal? Amazing. Outside the Battlements? Amazing. The Rim of Battle Mountain? Amazing. Fallen Blood? Best final boss theme ever. Every single track here is amazing, and you should listen to all of it.10/10 would listen to Fallen Blood for the fiftieth timesrsly, get this game, also is pretty funny.9/10 am playing several times again."
