,Recommended,265610,20048243,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,Bilbo,"A really fun, and funny game. I'm surprised by just how much I enjoyed this.The skills are cool, and some are amusing (Like dropping a tank on top of your enemies), and I was playing simply to unlock more skills to see what they were like.There isn't a lot of dialogue, and most of it's just random comments from the characters when you use new attacks are find something new, etc. Although not really bad in a game like this, it'd be better if there was more story to it, no matter how much seriousness said story lacks.It's not all that difficult if you play on normal, most enemies are some kind of creature crossed with an element, and so have weaknesses, you get a scan bot that lets you see said weaknesses so honestly as long as you don't forget to keep your weapons and skills diverse you're going to be fine. Each area generally has a focus on one or two elements, so you can focus on those with your weapons as well.The shop so far has been pretty pointless. I've not completed it yet, but I've literally only bought a few coffees from it before a boss, you don't really use items enough to use up the ones you find, and the weapons you find are generally good as well. Getting materials for crafting is simply a case of grinding as well.Better quests would be good, it seems all the npc's just want food, even just a ""kill n monsters"" or something would keep it more interesting. Just going out and fighting is fun enough in itself though, so it's not really a big issue.I feel like I've complained a bit about it, but despite everything I've said, the game is genuinly enjoyable, which is generally the biggest factor in a game."
